subsection.def:
DG(AE)R (《適用及豁免規例》)
                means the Dangerous Goods (Application and Exemption) Regulation 2012
                    (Cap. 295 sub. leg. E);

expressway
                    (快速公路) has the meaning assigned to it by
                    section 122 of the Road Traffic Ordinance (Cap. 374);

paragraph.content:
a vehicle being used by the Customs and Excise Department;
                        or (E.R. 1 of
                            2015)

subsection.def:
Cap. 374A (《第374A章》) means the Road Traffic
                (Construction and Maintenance of Vehicles) Regulations
                    (Cap. 374 sub. leg. A);

old requirement (舊規定) means the requirement indicated by Figure No. 6 traffic sign in
                accordance with the contents and the note relating to the traffic sign in the
                pre-amended Schedule;

subsection.content:
Class 1 indicates Class 1 dangerous goods (as defined by section
                        2 of the Dangerous Goods (Application and Exemption) Regulation
                        2012 (Cap. 295 sub. leg. E));

the display of a red cross indicates that the toll in respect of the
                    vehicle has not been paid and the vehicle must not proceed beyond or past the
                    signal;
